HEADWORD: Desman
<hw>Des"man</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧s"m⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sw.
<ets>desman</ets> musk.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An amphibious,
insectivorous mammal found in Russia (<spn>Myogale moschata</spn>). It
is allied to the moles, but is called <altname>muskrat</altname> by some
English writers.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>d⟦ae⟧sman</asp>.]</altsp></p>

